When a job fails to publish an artifact, the message in the logs is something like:

{noformat}
Unable to publish artifact [Webdriver screenshots]: null
{noformat}

The reason is always "null". This happens due to a bug in {{ArtifactPublishingResultImpl}}, which always returns a {{null}} from {{getFailureReason}}, and which ignores the actual reason string that's passed in by the {{failure}} factory method.

For plans we achieve this by using 

{code}
<web-item key="export" name="Sample" section="chain.actions/chainActions" weight="60">
{code}

But there's no such an extension point for deployment projects.

Bamboo cannot check out sub-modules if the sub-module URL format is set as the following.

{noformat}
git@github.organ.co.uk:ORG/repo.git
{noformat}

The same URL format works fine if used as the main repository URL.

I have marked this as critical because it works fine on Hudson and is providing a bit of a hurdle when migrating over to Bamboo

Currently, the output of the script task is not useful for debugging, as it does not show the commands that are executed.  Instead, the logs show something like:

{{/bin/sh /opt/app/atlassian/bamboo/current/temp/DEV-JOB1-8-ScriptBuildTask-6385738016401102851.sh}}

Rather than:
{{05:59:05 [atlas-web-promote] $ /bin/sh -xe /tmp/hudson1289015703492215660.sh}}
{{05:59:05 + ./my_script foo bar}}

Where a script is called using arguments generated dynamically, or pulled from Bamboo variables, this is essential.  Perhaps an option on the plugin that gives the equivalent of running under sh/ksh/bash -x?

The final task is not executed if the specific "Source checkout" task error below (for a Hg repo) occurs:

{noformat}
simple	25-Oct-2014 10:00:15	Cloning repository `/local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/_hg-repositories-cache/6753e14df42004e60ab7056d10788200f2caade9' to directory '/local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC'
simple	25-Oct-2014 10:00:16	Warning: failed to retrieve source code (com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.hg.HgCommandException: command /opt/mercurial/latest/hg clone --noupdate --config 'ui.ssh=ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o BatchMode=yes' /local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/_hg-repositories-cache/6753e14df42004e60ab7056d10788200f2caade9 /local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC failed. Working directory was `/local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC'. stderr: abort: destination '/local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC' is not empty stdout: ), trying to recover...
error	25-Oct-2014 10:00:16	Failed to clean source directory '/local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC' Unable to delete file: /local/atlassian/bamboo-home/xml-data/build-dir/LOAD-DES53-JOB1/MLC/deployTools/target/Releases/vMLC12_0_0/patches/3p/jacorb/2.3.1/source/jacorb-2.3.1-source.tar
{noformat}

The legacy stash integration will soon be deprecated as stated in this links: https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Stash#Stash-LegacyStashrepositoryintegration

We have mentioned in this [link|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Linking+to+source+code+repositories] that users using the local repo will have to use the linked repository type and that users will have to click the " Convert to linked repository". This can be quiet a mundane task for users will lots of plans.

It will be nice to have this feature as a bulk action.

*Workaround*
# Shutdown bamboo
# Run the command:
{code:sql}
update VCS_LOCATION set IS_GLOBAL=1;
{code}
# Restart bamboo
